---
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../../config";
import "../../styles/global.css";

// üîÅ CHANGE THESE PER PROJECT
const projectName = "PROJECT NAME ";
const projectTagline = "A floating picnic platform built under $100.";
const projectSummary =
  "DIY river-ready pontoon built from 55-gallon HDPE barrels and a reinforced frame, designed to carry a full picnic table and multiple passengers.";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>{projectName} | {siteConfig.name}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={projectSummary} />
  </head>

    <body class="bg-background text-foreground">
    <Header />

    <main class="pt-24 pb-16">
      <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-10">
        {/* Top header */}
        <header class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-blue-500">
            Project
          </p>
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-100">
            {projectName}
          </h1>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-gray-400">
            {projectTagline}
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-400">
            {projectSummary}
          </p>
        </header>

        {/* WHY ‚Äì Problem / Motivation / Constraints */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Why</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            {/* Replace this with the story: what problem you were solving,
                why this project existed, context (class, client, personal),
                and any hard constraints (budget, tools, timeline, safety, etc.) */}
            I wanted a way to turn a cheap, rough river float into a full picnic
            experience, under strict budget and material constraints.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>Goal: what ‚Äúsuccess‚Äù looked like.</li>
            <li>Constraints: budget, tools, material availability, deadlines.</li>
            <li>Users: who this was built for (you, friends, a client, a class).</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        {/* WHAT ‚Äì Concept, Requirements, High-level Architecture */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">What</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            {/* High-level concept and requirements */}
            At a high level, this project is a [device/system] that does X for Y,
            while satisfying Z constraints.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100">
            Key requirements
          </h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>Requirement 1 (e.g., must safely support 4 adults and a table).</li>
            <li>Requirement 2 (e.g., must stay under $100 in materials).</li>
            <li>Requirement 3 (e.g., must be buildable with basic shop tools).</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        {/* SCHEMATIC / PLAN ‚Äì first part of ‚ÄúHow‚Äù */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">
            Schematic &amp; Plan
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            {/* Explain the schematic / mechanical layout / circuit diagram / block diagram. */}
            The design started with a simple plan that balanced weight
            distribution, stability, and ease of assembly.
          </p>

          {/* If you have an image, drop it in /public/images/projects/... */}
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">
              Schematic / plan (placeholder):
            </p>
            <div class="aspect-[16/9] w-full rounded-xl border border-dashed border-slate-700 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-slate-500">
              {/* Replace this with an actual image tag: */}
              {/* <img src="/images/projects/pontoon-plan.png" alt="Pontoon plan" class="w-full h-full object-contain rounded-xl" /> */}
              Drop schematic or layout image here
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* COMPONENT SELECTION ‚Äì justify major parts */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">
            Component Selection
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            {/* Explain why you chose specific components / materials / ICs / mechanical parts. */}
            Each component was chosen to balance performance, cost, and ease of
            integration.
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-3">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100">
              Major components
            </h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>
                <span class="font-medium">Component / material 1</span> ‚Äî why you
                picked it over alternatives.
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="font-medium">Component / material 2</span> ‚Äî tradeoffs
                and reasoning.
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="font-medium">Component / material 3</span> ‚Äî reliability,
                availability, or safety considerations.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* BILL OF MATERIALS (BOM) */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">
            Bill of Materials (BOM)
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            {/* Quick note about total cost and any reuse/scavenged parts. */}
            The build was kept within budget by reusing materials where possible
            and choosing cost-effective components.
          </p>

          <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60">
            <table class="min-w-full text-sm text-left text-gray-300">
              <thead class="bg-slate-900/80 text-gray-200">
                <tr>
                  <th class="px-4 py-2">#</th>
                  <th class="px-4 py-2">Item</th>
                  <th class="px-4 py-2">Specification</th>
                  <th class="px-4 py-2">Qty</th>
                  <th class="px-4 py-2">Cost</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-800">
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">1</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">Example part</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">Size / rating / part number</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">x1</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">$0.00</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">2</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">Example part 2</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">Details here</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">x4</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">$0.00</td>
                </tr>
                {/* Duplicate rows as needed */}
                <tr class="bg-slate-900/60 font-semibold">
                  <td class="px-4 py-2" colspan="4">
                    Total
                  </td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-2">$0.00</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* HOW ‚Äì Build process & implementation */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">How</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            {/* High-level explanation of how you implemented the design. */}
            With the design locked and parts in hand, the build moved through
            fabrication, assembly, and testing.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100">
            Build process
          </h3>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>Step 1: prepare materials / cut stock / initial wiring.</li>
            <li>Step 2: assemble main structure / PCB / frame.</li>
            <li>Step 3: integrate components and perform basic checks.</li>
            <li>Step 4: final assembly, sealing, and safety checks.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        {/* TESTING & RESULTS */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">
            Testing &amp; Results
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            {/* Describe how you validated it: tests, metrics, real-world run. */}
            The system was tested in realistic conditions to verify stability,
            performance, and safety.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>Test scenario 1 and what you observed.</li>
            <li>Test scenario 2: edge cases, overloads, or failure modes.</li>
            <li>Final outcome: did it meet or exceed the original ‚ÄúWhy‚Äù.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        {/* LESSONS / NEXT STEPS */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">
            What I&apos;d Do Next
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            {/* Short reflection: what you‚Äôd change, next iteration ideas, or how this feeds other projects. */}
            With more time and budget, I would iterate on durability and user
            experience, and explore how to turn this into a repeatable build.
          </p>
        </section>

        {/* Back link */}
        <div class="pt-4">
          <a
            href="/projects"
            class="text-sm text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline-offset-2 hover:underline"
          >
            ‚Üê Back to all projects
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
